# GETTING STARTED — BITOS

> Pocket AI companion device. Pi Zero 2W + Whisplay HAT + PiSugar 3.
> Hold the button. Speak. Claude answers through the speaker.

---

## What You Need

### Hardware
| Part | Notes |
|---|---|
| Raspberry Pi Zero 2W | 512MB RAM, ARM Cortex-A53 |
| Whisplay HAT | 240×280 LCD + WM8960 audio codec |
| PiSugar 3 | Battery + pogo-pin power connector |
| microSD card | 32GB+, Class 10/A2 |
| USB-C cable | For charging via PiSugar |

### Accounts & Keys
- Anthropic API key — [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com)
- GitHub account with SSH key configured

### Mac (for flashing)
- Pi Imager — [raspberrypi.com/software](https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/)
- Git + SSH key (`~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub`)

---

## Physical Assembly

Stack order (bottom to top):



[ PiSugar 3      ]  ← battery, USB-C charge port
[ Pi Zero 2W     ]  ← pogo pins connect to PiSugar
[ Whisplay HAT   ]  ← seats on GPIO header (all 40 pins)


**Important:**
- PiSugar connects via 6 pogo pins on the underside — press firmly until flush
- Whisplay HAT pins must be fully seated — check orientation before pressing
- Power button is on PiSugar, not Pi
- Charge via USB-C on PiSugar only

**Expected I2C addresses (verify after boot):**


0x57 — PiSugar 3 battery
0x1A — WM8960 audio codec


