## One-Time Mac Setup

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone git@github.com:sabi-c/bitos.git
cd bitos


2. Add your SSH key to cloud-init

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub  # copy this output

nano scripts/cloud-init/user-data
# → Replace YOUR_SSH_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE with your key
# → Replace YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME with your GitHub username


3. That’s it — you’re ready to flash

Flash the SD Card
Step 1 — Flash with Pi Imager
Open Pi Imager → choose:
	∙	OS: Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit, Bookworm)
	∙	Storage: your SD card
	∙	Gear icon (Advanced):
	∙	Hostname: bitos
	∙	Enable SSH: yes
	∙	WiFi SSID + password: your network
	∙	Locale: your timezone
Click Write and wait.
Step 2 — Copy cloud-init (do this before ejecting)

make flash


This copies the auto-install config to the SD card and ejects it safely. The script will warn you if your SSH key hasn’t been added yet.
Step 3 — Insert SD and power on
	∙	Insert SD card into Pi Zero 2W
	∙	Press the PiSugar power button (hold 1-2 seconds)
	∙	Wait 15 minutes — auto-install runs on first boot
The boot screen will appear on the Whisplay HAT display showing install progress.

First Boot Setup
SSH in after 15 minutes:

ssh pi@bitos
# or: ssh pi@bitos.local


Run the first-boot script — it handles everything:

bash ~/bitos/scripts/day_one.sh


This script:
	1.	Verifies all hardware (display, button, audio, I2C)
	2.	Checks secrets configuration
	3.	Prompts you to add your Anthropic API key if missing
	4.	Starts both services (bitos-server + bitos-device)
	5.	Runs smoke test to confirm end-to-end connectivity
Adding your API key when prompted:

sudo nano /etc/bitos/secrets
# Add this line:
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Save: Ctrl+X → Y → Enter


After day_one.sh completes:
	∙	Display shows boot diagnostics (all green)
	∙	Lock screen appears
	∙	Default PIN: 0000

First Voice Interaction
	1.	Unlock: Enter PIN 0000 using button gestures
	2.	Navigate to Chat: SHORT press to scroll, LONG press to select
	3.	Speak: Hold button (LONG press) → speak → release
	4.	Listen: Claude responds through the speaker

