Troubleshooting
See docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md for the full decision tree.
Quick fixes:



|Symptom              |Fix                                               |
|---------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
|Screen blank         |`sudo raspi-config nonint do_spi 0 && sudo reboot`|
|No audio             |`cd ~/whisplay && sudo bash install.sh`           |
|Button unresponsive  |Check GPIO Board pin 11 reads 0 when pressed      |
|Claude offline       |`bash scripts/setup/check_secrets.sh`             |
|Services not starting|`make logs` to see error                          |
|Wrong I2C addresses  |`sudo i2cdetect -y 1` — expect 0x57 and 0x1A      |

Hardware verify (run on Pi):

python scripts/verify_hardware.py


Full smoke test:

python scripts/smoke_test.py


Architecture

Pi Zero 2W (device)
  └── Pygame/ST7789 display
  └── WM8960 audio (record + playback)
  └── GPIO button (single button, gesture detection)
  └── BLE GATT server (companion pairing)
  └── HTTP client → FastAPI server
  
Mac mini (server)
  └── FastAPI server (:8000)
  └── LLM bridge (Anthropic / OpenClaw / any OpenAI-compatible)
  └── Vikunja adapter (task management)
  └── Morning brief worker (8am daily context)


The Pi handles display, input, and audio. All intelligence runs on the Mac mini. Swap LLM providers with one .env change.

Environment Variables
Copy .env.template to .env and configure:

# Required
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Server (Mac mini)
SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8000
LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic        # anthropic / openclaw / echo

# Device hardware
BITOS_DISPLAY=pygame          # pygame (desktop) / st7789 (Pi)
BITOS_AUDIO=mock              # mock (desktop) / hw:0 (Pi)
BITOS_BUTTON=keyboard         # keyboard (desktop) / gpio (Pi)

# Optional integrations
VIKUNJA_URL=http://localhost:3456/api/v1
VIKUNJA_API_TOKEN=            # leave empty for demo tasks
OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH=          # path to your Obsidian vault


On the Pi, secrets live in /etc/bitos/secrets (root-owned, not in git).

